The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Friday, April 23, 2004  Business Briefs																								 Basel (Switzerland), April 22: Swiss drug giant Novartis said today it will discuss a possible merger deal with its French-German counterpart Aventis, which is battling to ward off a takeover bid from a French rival. Demonstrating its muscle, Novartis also announced a 22 per cent jump in first quarter profit and pledged record full-year results. The board of Novartis has decided to accept the offer of the Aventis supervisory board to negotiate conditions for a potential business combination, the firm said in a statement.																								 New Delhi, April 22: Ashok Leyland today said it would issue foreign currency convertible notes to raise $100 million from overseas markets.																								 New Delhi, April 22: India will be represented by disinvestment minister Arun Shourie in the informal ministerial meeting convened by US trade representative Robert Zoellick in London end of this month.																								 Mumbai, April 22: Larsen amp; Toubro said today the Bombay High Court has cleared the demerger plan of its cement business into Ultra Tech Cemco Ltd.																								 Mumbai, April 22: Talks have begun between the Indian and foreign lenders of Dabhol Power Co in Singapore to buy out the latters debt exposure of over $310 million.																								 Mumbai, April 22: The BSE and the NSE will be closed on April 26 in view of the Lok Sabha elections in Mumbai on that day.
